<TITLE> Dhaka gets zonewise 'weekends' to ease traffic </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 1 (bdnews24.com)The government has divided Dhaka into seven zones with shops and businesses in each to observe a different weekly holiday, in a further measure to combat the capital's chronic traffic gridlock. The decision came at a cabinet meeting on Monday, the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told reporters. It will come into effect soon, he said. The zone-wise holidays are as follows ( Click here to see zone demarcations) : Zone 1- Friday full holiday and Saturday half holiday Zone 2- Sunday full holiday and Monday half holiday Zone 3- Thursday full holiday and Friday half Zone 4-Tuesday full holiday and Wednesday half Zone 5-Thursday full and Friday half Zone 6- Sunday full and Monday half Zone 7- Wednesday full and Thursday half A half-day holiday means markets and businesses can remain open up to 2pm. During working days they will remain open until 8pm as usual. Monday's cabinet meeting also cancelled a decision of an interim cabinet meeting held in March, 2007, as an agreement of the Multilateral Sub-regional Economic Co-operation was not signed. It discussed the climate conference held in Copenhagen last December and next steps. It also welcomes the execution on Jan 28 of five detained convicts for the 1975 muder of Sheikh Mujibur Rahman. bd
